speech.p:
That, for the purpose of any Act resulting from the Building Societies Bill, it is expendient to authorize—


(1) the levying of annual charges on authorised building societies towards the expenses of the Building Societies Commission established by that Act;

(2) the imposition of charges to corporation tax by provisions relating to the treatment for the purpose of the Tax Acts of payments made to building societies by the Building Societies Investor Protection Board established by that Act;

(3) The payment into the Consolidated Fund of any sums falling to be paid into that Fund in pursuance of that Act.—[Mr. Maude.]
